HEADWORD: Indument
<hw>In"du*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indumentum</ets> a covering. See <er>Indue</er>, and cf.
<er>Induement</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Plumage;
feathers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot., Zool.)</fld> <def>A dense covering,
especially a hairy one; called also
<altname>indumentum</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

